{
  "texts": [
    "Table 9 depicts our experimental settings and results for the generic dataset G-PNDA.",
    "We train a model for each dataset part, and the multi-task learning models MULT ALL Table 9 shows that the proposed MULT GRP model outperforms all other settings.",
    "Surprisingly, sharing the output layer impairs performance in all settings.",
    "We can attribute this to the fact that the output layer learns different transition distributions between the classes.Thus, in a domain-independent setting a separate output layer per dataset part helps to capture the individual rhetorical structure of the domains (#RQ3, #RQ6).",
    "Automatic Domain-Independent Clustering: To further validate the quality of the calculated semantic vectors for different annotation schemes, we conducted an additional experiment apart from the visual analysis performed before."
  ]
